@DATABASE Objects.Menu

@NODE MAIN "Menu: Objects"

 Type                   >>
    @{" Object 1           " link TOB1}  Select object 1 for placement.
    @{" Object 2           " link TOB2}  Select object 2 for placement.
    @{" Object 3           " link TOB3}  Select object 3 for placement.
    @{" Object 4           " link TOB4}  Select object 4 for placement.
    @{" Object 5           " link TOB5}  Select object 5 for placement.
    @{" Object 6           " link TOB6}  Select object 6 for placement.
    @{" $100               " link C100}  Select $100 cash for placement.
    @{" $500               " link C500}  Select $500 cash for placement.
    @{" Other Amount...    " link CAMT}  Select another cash amount for placement.

    @{" Adjust Cash Height " link ACHI}  Adjusts the height of cash placed.

 Edit Object            >>
    @{" 1...               " link EOBJ}  Edit object 1 information.
    @{" 2...               " link EOBJ}  Edit object 2 information.
    @{" 3...               " link EOBJ}  Edit object 3 information.
    @{" 4...               " link EOBJ}  Edit object 4 information.
    @{" 5...               " link EOBJ}  Edit object 5 information.
    @{" 6...               " link EOBJ}  Edit object 6 information.

@{" Edit Cash Height...    " link ECHI}  Edit the height cash is placed at.

@ENDNODE

@NODE TOB1 "Objects/Object 1"

  This selects object 1 for placement when in @{" Edit Objects " link Mode.Menu/OBJS} mode.

  @{B}Note:@{UB} You must edit & define the object before you can select it.

  For more information on objects see @{" Objects " link "Describe.Menu/Objects"}.

@ENDNODE

